<br>
Just a quick post to remind everyone that the civility of the Rathe server only exists with the cooperation of the guilds that it serves. We, as representatives, should be at the front lines of guiding our guilds into actions that promote the things this game are supposed to be about: fun, and interactions with others through the game as a medium. <br>
<br>
The majority of posters in this forum are officers and leaders in their respective guilds; holding such a position carries responcibility that I know I don't need to explain to you all. <br>
<br>
Inasmuch as I enjoy flaming on the boards, please understand that board related flames stay on the boards, and game related flames are fueled more by bordom than anything else. When people log in, I am of the belief that all but the most sadistic player is logging in to have fun. <br>
<br>
There does exist, in a game of this kind, a duty that every player has to every other player; therefore, the golden rule should apply to your decisions in game. Would you appreciate the behavior that you are showing others? If not, perhaps you should reevaluate what it is you are doing, and why it is you are doing it. If this is 'just' a game, than why would you ruin it for someone? And if this is more than 'just' a game, please remember to take the enjoyment people get out of it seriously. Sure, it may not always be returned, but it can only be made better if people try to act like human beings. <br>
<br>
No, I'm not about to break into a rant about who did what to who. I'm asking, politely, for those of us in these forums to take back to our guilds a message that people should be respected on the server, in large groups and individually, on both real life lines and in game lines. <br>
<br>
As the leaders on the Rathe, we all owe it to each other, no matter if we like each other or not, to advance an environment which is fun for everyone to be a part of, and play in. That means being aware of what is a 'rule' and what is 'being reasonable', as well as respecting a person when they ask you to leave them alone. Harassment is certainly a bannable offense, and breaking either the spirit or the 'law' of RTA conventions, in all reality, should be. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
As representatives of our respective guilds, the actions of the people in our guilds online reflects on us; we should be worried about that, not uncaring, and certainly not dismissive. <br>
<br>
Especially in light of the recent hard feelings on the flame boards, lets remember that people go into a game to escape the stresses of daily life; that includes the arguments of the flame board about things that don't pertain to the game. <br>
<br>
I'm not asking us to dissolve into an orgy of hugs and kisses and flowery goodness; just to remember, and remind the people in your guilds, that each other character you see is another human being who is trying to enjoy the game, and that there is no real reason to make life difficult for them, just as you would rather people didn't make life difficult for you. <br>
<br>
Take care,<br>
